name: Galactic Domination Online
blurb: An epic space strategy MMO set in the Galactic Third Age. Colonize, conquer, trade, research. Forge an empire from the rim to the core.

rewards.reward: 1. Your name on the backer page (All levels get this)\r\n2. Access To Message Boards\r\n3. Pledge amount in Galactic Domination Virtual Credit - Used in game to shop in the LDVC Galactic Bazaar.

1.	Beta Testing Access
2.	Message Board / Forum Access
3.	Pledge amount in Galactic Domination Virtual Credit - Used in game to shop in the LDVC Galactic Bazaar.
4.	Periodic Newsletter(s) from the Developer via Email

1.\tAll of the $25 benefits\r\n2.\t\u201cSystem Naming\u201d. The name you provide will be added to a list in the Galaxy Generator Tool, and given a \u201cpriority flag\u201d. When a new Galaxy is generated, the tool will draw from the flagged names first, and a solar system will be given the name you provided. Astronomical odds are in your favor for your named system to be in a different location in every persistent Galaxy played.

1.\tAll of the $25 benefits\r\n2.\t"Monster Naming" The name you provide will be added to a list in the database which is randomly drawn from. The name is appended to random encounter \u201cmonster\u201d within the game. If you choose, the game will email each time your "monster" appears in any galaxy (what Galaxy, the sector location, and the description of the encounter). Example, a derelict space vessel: Your sensors detect an ancient derelict battle-cruiser adrift in this sector. Its markings indicate that it is the USF Your Name, a Human vessel from the Galactic Second Age.

1.	All of the $25 benefits
2.	Backer T-shirt
3.	Cool Queue Studios Galactic Domination Online Poster autographed by Scott Quiggle and the rest of the project team.
4.	System AND Monster Naming.

1.\tAll of the $25 benefits\r\n2.\t"Character Naming". The LDVC Galactic Bazaar provides clones of great leaders, for a price. This is your opportunity to name a Famous Captain, General, Scientist, or Governor after yourself or your loved one (or anything you want as long as it meets guidelines). There are 400 characters, 25 of each of four types from each of the four races available to choose from. The picking of types and races will be in the order of received contributions at this level. You will also receive the character that you have named in game play for each galaxy you play in,  at no cost.  Limited Quantity.\r\n3.\tA signed art print (by the artist who drew the character) of the Character you have named.

1.\tAll of the $25 benefits\r\n2.\t"Vessel Class Naming". Each race, including the Core, has 20 Classes of ships ranging from fighters and scouts, to Battleships and Dreadnaughts.  This is your opportunity to name a class of Vessel after yourself or your loved one (or anything you want as long as it meets guidelines). On a first come, first serve basis, you may choose the race and class of vessel from any of the four races or the Core. Limited Quantity.\r\n3.\tYou will receive an art print of the vessel class you have named, signed by the artist.

1. All of the $25 benefits
2. Backer T-shirt
3. “Elite Character Art”.  This is your opportunity to not only name (as in the $500 level), but also have your likeness imposed on a special, elite level character from any of the four playable races.  If you choose to be non-human, understand that it will be the artist’s creative interpretation / rendition of you as that race. You must provide a clear non-copyrighted headshot photo and be legally able to provide said photo, which we will approve/disapprove before the artwork is commissioned. You will also receive the character with your likeness in game play for each galaxy that you play in, at no cost. 
4. You will receive the original art composition of your character, signed by the artist.

1.	All of the $25 benefits

3.	‘Elite Character Art” from the $2,500 level.
4.	An invitation (you and a guest) to the Cool Queue Studios / Galactic Domination Online private Launch Party in San Diego, CA. Rub elbows with Scott Quiggle and other key members of CQS. (must be able to provide own travel and accommodations to San Diego, CA, USA)
